intro: Swainsona cadellii, commonly known as the Cadell's swainsona, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the legume family, Fabaceae, and is characterized by its distinctive yellow flowers with a prominent keel. The plant typically grows in arid or semi-arid regions, adapting to harsh environmental conditions. Its leaves are compound, consisting of several small leaflets, and it produces pods that contain seeds. Swainsona cadellii is often found in sandy soils and is an important component of local ecosystems.
